setwd("~/Desktop/KSE/Econometrics III")
df <- read_excel("quarterly.xls") %>% 
  select(DATE, Tbill, r5) %>% 
  mutate(
    st = r5 - Tbill,
    DATE = str_replace(DATE, pattern="Q", replacement = "-0") %>% 
      as_date(format = "%Y-%m")
    )

  print((paste("BIC = ", as.character(ur.df2(df$st, lags = i, type = "trend")$bic))))
  print_empty_line()
}

With the 5% significance, test statistics are always bigger than corresponding critical values. So, the # of lags in the model does not matter in this case because H0 is rejected with any number of lags.

Calculate bias

Procedure:

Find the volatility by subtracting forecasted value from the real value, build a regression, where y = volatility from the previous point and, x = forecasted value. Evaluate the regression. If B0 is insignificant or equal to 0 and B1 is insignificant or equal to 1, then there is no bias

volat_ar7 <- data2_check$spread - pred_ar7$mean
mean(volat_ar7)
## [1] 0.1267391
lm_ar7 <- lm(volat_ar7 ~ pred_ar7$mean)
summary(lm_ar7) #there is no bias in the model ar7

There is no bias in the models ar7 and arma2_7.

Calculate MSPE and GN statistics

z <- volat_ar7 - volat_arma2_7
x <- volat_ar7 + volat_arma2_7
r <- cor(x,z)
gn_test <- r/(((1-(r)^2)/(length(volat_ar7)-1))^(1/2))
print(paste("GN statistics =", as.character(gn_test)))
## [1] "GN statistics = -0.611709124175802"
#for ar7:
MSPE_ar7 <- mean((volat_ar7)^2)
print(paste("MSPE for AR(7) =", as.character(MSPE_ar7)))
## [1] "MSPE for AR(7) = 0.746195485809337"
#for arma(2,(1,7))
MSPE_arima2_7 <- mean((volat_arma2_7)^2)
print(paste("MSPE for ARIMA(2,0,(1,7)) =", as.character(MSPE_arima2_7)))
## [1] "MSPE for ARIMA(2,0,(1,7)) = 0.752675413647734"

Calculate RMSE, MAE and MAPE

#RMSE for ar7:
RMSE_ar7 <- (sum((volat_ar7)^2/length((volat_ar7)))^(1/2))
print(paste("RMSE for AR(7) =", as.character(RMSE_ar7)))
## [1] "RMSE for AR(7) = 0.863826073818877"
#for arma(2,(1,7)):
RMSE_arima2_7 <- (sum((volat_arma2_7)^2/length((volat_arma2_7)))^(1/2))
print(paste("RMSE for ARIMA(2,0,(1,7)) =", as.character(RMSE_arima2_7)))
## [1] "RMSE for ARIMA(2,0,(1,7)) = 0.867568679499055"
#MAE and MAPE:

#Mean absolute error (MAE) and mean absolute percentage error (MAPE):

#MAE for ar7:
MAE_ar7 <- sum(abs(volat_ar7))/length(volat_ar7)
print(paste("MAE for AR(7) =", as.character(MAE_ar7)))
## [1] "MAE for AR(7) = 0.756462252409613"
#for arma(2,(1,7)):
MAE_arima2_7 <- sum(abs(volat_arma2_7))/length(volat_arma2_7)
print(paste("MAE for ARIMA(2,0,(1,7)) =", as.character(MAE_arima2_7)))
## [1] "MAE for ARIMA(2,0,(1,7)) = 0.759559610118861"
#MAPE for ar7:
MAPE_ar7 <- sum(abs(data2_check$spread - pred_ar7$mean/data2_check$spread))/length(data2_check$spread)
print(paste("MAPE for AR(7) =", as.character(MAPE_ar7)))
## [1] "MAPE for AR(7) = 4.0787030706585"
#for arma(2,(1,7)):
MAPE_arima2_7 <- sum(abs(data2_check$spread - pred_arma2_7$mean/data2_check$spread))/length(data2_check$spread)
print(paste("MAPE for ARIMA(2,0,(1,7)) =", as.character(MAPE_arima2_7)))
## [1] "MAPE for ARIMA(2,0,(1,7)) = 4.0084837431281"

GARCH (50%)

data1 <- read_xls("quarterly.xls")

data2 <- data1 %>% 
  select(., c("DATE","r5","Tbill")) %>% 
  mutate(DATE = yearquarter(data1$DATE))

data2$spread <- data1$r5 - data1$Tbill 
data2 <- as_tsibble(data2, index = "DATE")

arima2_7 <- arima(data2$spread, order=c(2,0,7), fixed = c(NA,NA,NA,0,0,0,0,0,NA,NA))
summary(arima2_7)
